1
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:27,280
(In Mourning)

2
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:32,479
(In Mourning)

3
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:35,519
(Sino-Japanese Trade Association
Appointment Ceremony)

4
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:38,219
(Letter of Appointment)

5
00:00:38,220 --> 00:00:41,300
Congratulations, you're the president
of the Japanese Chamber of Commerce now.

6
00:00:55,780 --> 00:00:57,020
Miss?

7
00:00:57,740 --> 00:00:58,940
Miss.

8
00:00:59,620 --> 00:01:01,820
You're back, miss.

9
00:01:07,340 --> 00:01:08,540
Miss.

10
00:01:16,660 --> 00:01:19,180
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations, President Shen.

11
00:01:20,980 --> 00:01:22,020
Congratulations.

12
00:01:26,340 --> 00:01:27,940
Miss Lin is back.

13
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:32,119
=Echoes of Gang City=

14
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:36,280
=Episode 10=
(The Last Meeting)

15
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:29,900
It was you

16
00:02:31,260 --> 00:02:33,940
who had people hide the news
of my father's death from me.

17
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:36,500
Yes.

18
00:02:39,380 --> 00:02:41,780
You took over the Lin family business.

19
00:02:43,780 --> 00:02:44,980
Yes.

20
00:02:46,620 --> 00:02:49,900
You're the new president
of the Sino-Japanese Chamber of Commerce.

21
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:53,420
Yes.

22
00:03:12,380 --> 00:03:13,740
I, Lin Shuyi,

23
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:17,700
from this day on, cut all ties with you.

24
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:20,080
No matter how many lifetimes
there may be,

25
00:03:21,340 --> 00:03:22,740
we are through for good.

26
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:32,600
(Former Fiancé)

27
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:44,180
Get out!

28
00:03:53,380 --> 00:03:55,620
Miss Lin, Mr. Shen...

29
00:04:16,820 --> 00:04:18,020
And this.

30
00:04:18,832 --> 00:04:20,380
Mr. Fu said

31
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:22,380
it was once a whole piece.

32
00:04:22,780 --> 00:04:24,700
But now the broken jade
can never be whole again.

33
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,140
He's done his best to repair it.

34
00:04:27,380 --> 00:04:30,780
He hopes you'll still find
a good match in the future.

35
00:04:56,980 --> 00:04:59,540
Mr. Shen, this is rude.

36
00:04:59,580 --> 00:05:00,940
Things have been tense lately.

37
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:02,699
You should stop your operation for now.

38
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:05,299
We've broken off the engagement.

39
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:06,420
What I do

40
00:05:07,180 --> 00:05:08,420
is none of your business.

41
00:05:12,460 --> 00:05:15,500
Perfect. Take it back.

42
00:06:05,380 --> 00:06:08,019
Gathering all the businessmen here
and threatening them

43
00:06:08,020 --> 00:06:10,300
is an insult to our national pride.

44
00:06:10,580 --> 00:06:13,499
We're all doing our best
to resist and push back.

45
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:16,900
We will never forget our principles.

46
00:06:17,180 --> 00:06:18,500
This is a small token from us.

47
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:26,900
Mr. Shen.

48
00:06:28,380 --> 00:06:30,099
Since your appointment,

49
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:33,779
trade between our harbors
has been running more smoothly.

50
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:38,580
It's just that shipping
through Xiangshao Harbor has declined.

51
00:06:40,460 --> 00:06:43,180
The Xiangshao route
is Gang City's matter.

52
00:06:43,420 --> 00:06:45,259
If you can't handle it,

53
00:06:45,260 --> 00:06:46,900
there's even less I can do.

54
00:06:47,180 --> 00:06:48,380
But don't worry.

55
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,899
The chamber will step in to assist,

56
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:52,220
mediate wherever possible,

57
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:54,219
and help everyone

58
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:55,340
through this.

59
00:06:56,580 --> 00:06:58,459
It's a fine evening.

60
00:06:58,460 --> 00:07:00,899
Let's set everything aside

61
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:02,100
and enjoy ourselves.

62
00:07:02,580 --> 00:07:05,100
I'm reassured by your words.

63
00:07:08,980 --> 00:07:11,179
Mr. Shen, Miss Lin is here.

64
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,300
They

65
00:07:12,860 --> 00:07:14,140
are here too.

66
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:18,740
Thank you for your donations.

67
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:21,700
I thank you on behalf
of all the children at the orphanage.

68
00:07:23,020 --> 00:07:24,979
Miss Lin, be careful.

69
00:07:24,980 --> 00:07:25,940
Let's go.

70
00:07:36,620 --> 00:07:37,740
Who are you?

71
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:44,140
Mr. Shen asked to speak with you.

72
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:19,180
You're injured.

73
00:08:21,420 --> 00:08:23,540
Mr. Shen, you should
take care of yourself.

74
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:26,420
You're concerned about me?

75
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:30,740
There are more than just me
who want you dead now.

76
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:33,380
I'd rather you not die
at someone else's hands.

77
00:08:41,380 --> 00:08:42,700
You're insane!

78
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:48,180
You chose this path.

79
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:49,579
You should know

80
00:08:49,580 --> 00:08:51,220
nothing will happen between us.

81
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:08,900
You attend so many charity banquets
every day.

82
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:10,540
Are you not tired?

83
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:21,820
You might as well marry me.

84
00:09:22,380 --> 00:09:24,100
You can have anything you want.

85
00:09:26,380 --> 00:09:27,820
I'd rather die

86
00:09:29,060 --> 00:09:31,300
than have anything to do with you.

87
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:04,779
Mr. Shen,

88
00:10:04,780 --> 00:10:08,300
those people were here
to assassinate Miss Lin.

89
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:10,900
Why not you tell her the truth

90
00:10:11,780 --> 00:10:14,300
so she can protect herself?

91
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:18,020
She knows exactly what she's facing.

92
00:10:19,780 --> 00:10:22,540
But every extra charity ticket she sells

93
00:10:23,020 --> 00:10:25,900
means thirty more crates
of medical supplies for the front line.

94
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:29,740
Shuyi won't give up.

95
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:31,900
What about you?

96
00:10:36,180 --> 00:10:37,300
Me?

97
00:10:40,820 --> 00:10:43,060
I look like a lost cause now.

98
00:10:43,580 --> 00:10:45,100
If she stays tied to me,

99
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:48,100
she'll only face more danger.

100
00:10:49,901 --> 00:10:51,661
I understand.

101
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:54,700
It's just hard to accept.

102
00:11:06,220 --> 00:11:08,180
When everything is over,

103
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:10,740
I'll ask for her forgiveness.

104
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:13,900
I believe that day won't be far.

105
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:16,940
It won't be long.

106
00:11:21,580 --> 00:11:23,059
Headline!

107
00:11:23,060 --> 00:11:25,500
(Discount)
Two dead in the dance hall.

108
00:11:25,580 --> 00:11:28,700
City on lockdown. Killer at large.

109
00:11:28,860 --> 00:11:30,179
Headline!

110
00:11:30,180 --> 00:11:32,499
Two dead in the dance hall.

111
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:35,740
City on lockdown. Killer at large.

112
00:11:40,180 --> 00:11:41,580
What's wrong?

113
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:44,320
(Assassinate Lin Shuyi tonight)

114
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:46,300
Inform Mr. Zhou now.

115
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,580
Watch out!

116
00:12:15,980 --> 00:12:16,819
Madam Liu, come here!

117
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:19,379
Miss!

118
00:12:19,380 --> 00:12:20,140
Let's go.

119
00:12:23,940 --> 00:12:25,300
What do we do now?

120
00:12:29,580 --> 00:12:30,299
Keep a close watch.

121
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:30,979
Orders from above.

122
00:12:30,980 --> 00:12:32,500
She must die tonight.

123
00:12:34,660 --> 00:12:36,740
What are you doing here, Mr. Shen?

124
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:39,580
Go through the back door.

125
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:42,490
♪Tonight the rain falls soft and slow♪

126
00:13:43,770 --> 00:13:49,570
♪Blending with letters left unread
drifting through the air♪

127
00:13:50,290 --> 00:13:55,650
♪You turn and look back at me♪

128
00:13:56,770 --> 00:14:02,290
♪In those same eyes familiar tears
quietly appear♪

129
00:14:03,130 --> 00:14:08,770
♪It feels like we have carried so much♪

130
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:15,530
♪So many questions time itself
could not make clear♪

131
00:14:16,650 --> 00:14:21,970
♪The moment you walked into my life♪

132
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:28,930
♪Every dream I had became something
I want with you near♪

133
00:14:29,330 --> 00:14:36,290
♪How many letters have I written
just for you?♪

134
00:14:36,410 --> 00:14:42,090
♪If only you could truly hear
what my heart is trying to say♪

135
00:14:42,770 --> 00:14:49,129
♪From this life on no distance
could keep us apart♪

136
00:14:49,130 --> 00:14:52,009
♪The promise we made♪

137
00:14:52,010 --> 00:14:55,689
♪Will find its way to be fulfilled
one day♪

138
00:14:55,690 --> 00:15:02,289
♪But I want more
than just that fleeting gaze♪

139
00:15:02,290 --> 00:15:08,690
♪Still I have not heard your answer♪

140
00:15:09,090 --> 00:15:15,409
♪Can we still rewrite the ending
we face?♪

141
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:20,530
♪When regrets begin to turn around you
will hear it all♪

142
00:15:21,010 --> 00:15:24,010
♪Everything that leads me back to you♪
